Problem statement :-¶

As a Data scientist at Euroticket.com , our startup company aiming to enhance user experience and the engagement by leveraging the IMDB movie reviews through sentiment analysis ,Here the main task is using Natural Language Processing and Machine Learning techniques we need to develop a robust sentiment analysis end-to-end pipeline that accurately classifies IMDB movie reviews as Negative or Positive based on the textual content provided and here we have 5000 movies data from IMDB website. This model will enable EuroTicket.com to provide their users with insightful sentimental information, enhancing movie recommendation systems and improving overall customer satisfaction. Here we are going to follow the below processes:-

Removing the html-tags and junkdata from review column:-¶
In [12]:
def remove_junk(raw_text):
    cleaned_text= re.sub(r'[^a-zA-Z0-9\s]','',raw_text)
    return cleaned_text
In [13]:
df_movie['review']=df_movie['review'].apply(remove_junk)
In [ ]:
df_movie['review'][1]

Text preprocessing 🛞¶

In [19]:
stop_words = set(stopwords.words('english'))
In [20]:
## applying the stemming and wordtokenizer for the review column
def preprocess_text(text):
    wordz=nltk.word_tokenize(text) #tokenizing
    wordz=[content for content in wordz if content not in stop_words]
    return ' '.join(wordz)

df_movie['review'].apply(preprocess_text)

In [21]:
df_movie['review']=df_movie['review'].apply(preprocess_text)

The summary of performance of our model with different text preperocessing techniques and traditional machine learning models is as shown below

The accuracy score using GaussianNB and Bag of words is 74.11%
The accuracy score using RandomForestclassifier and Bag of words is 85.32%
The accuracy score using RandomForestclassifier and TFIDF is 85.2%
The accuracy score using RandomForestclassifier with hyperparametric tuning and N-grams is 82.73%

from this above results we can see that our model is performing well using RandomForestclassifier with TFIDF and Bag of words.

The Confusion matrix using RandomForestclassifier and TFIDF showing better results compared to others
